Dynamic Universe: In live trading, subscribing to all ~1,000+ USDT pairs on Binance for real-time 15-minute bars is memory-intensive. 
A better approach is to have your Nautilus strategy first load the full list of instruments from the exchange. 
Then, it can apply your initial filters (like excluding stablecoins or low-volatility pairs, similar to your ListFilter) 
to create a smaller "active watchlist" of ~100-200 high-potential pairs.


